---
// Byline for recipe posts — distinct wording from WinnieByline (blog posts).
// Winnie is a disclosed AI/virtual host with no real cooking history (see
// Character-Bible.md), so this must never imply she personally developed,
// tested, or has a family history with a recipe. Recipes are credited to the
// Nest & Nook kitchen team; Winnie narrates tips/voice, same honest framing
// used sitewide.
---
<div class="winnie-byline">
  <img src="/winnie/avatar.jpg" alt="Winnie Hollowell" width="76" height="76" />
  <div>
    <p class="name">Recipe by the Nest &amp; Nook Kitchen Team <span class="role">— narrated by Winnie Hollowell</span></p>
    <p class="disclosure-line">Winnie is a virtual, AI-generated spokesperson, not a real person — she's not the one who developed or tested this recipe. That's our real editorial team, using standard, well-established ratios and techniques. <a href="/about/#meet-winnie">What does that mean?</a></p>
  </div>
</div>

<style>
  .winnie-byline {
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    align-items: flex-start;
    margin: 0 0 1.75rem;
  }
  .winnie-byline img {
    border-radius: 50%;
    object-fit: cover;
    box-shadow: 0 0 0 2px var(--gold);
    flex: none;
  }
  .winnie-byline .name {
    margin: 0 0 0.2rem;
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--ink);
  }
  .winnie-byline .role {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
  }
  .winnie-byline .disclosure-line {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    max-width: 52ch;
  }
  .winnie-byline .disclosure-line a { color: var(--ink-soft); font-weight: 600; }
</style>
